## Findings
1. [P1] Fix 1 config still uses the old 4-button request model - `pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx:1795-1806` still defines `HELP_REQUEST_TYPES` as `call_waiter/bill/napkins/menu/other`, keeps the old cooldown map, and `HELP_CARD_LABELS` still maps the legacy `bill/menu` labels instead of the v6.0 `get_bill/plate/utensils/clear_table` set. `pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx:2130` also keeps `nonOtherTypes` on the same old list. This means the new preset request types would be filtered out of normalization/server-sync and never participate in the preset flow. FIX: replace the constants with the six-button v6.0 set, add legacy-only `menu` only where specified, add `HELP_CARD_SHORT_LABELS`, and update `nonOtherTypes` to include `plate`, `utensils`, and `clear_table`.
2. [P1] Fix 1 removal targets are still live dependencies in this baseline - `HELP_PREVIEW_LIMIT` is still used at `pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx:2701`, `pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx:4935`, and `pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx:5027`, and `HELP_CHIPS` is still rendered at `pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx:5102`. The task requires both identifiers to reach 0 occurrences while also forbidding JSX changes, but in the current file these references are not isolated to the constants block. FIX: either expand scope to remove/update the render references in the same task, or keep these symbols until the JSX task that replaces their consumers lands.
3. [P2] Fix 2 urgency thresholds and helper callbacks are missing entirely - after `HELP_COOLDOWN_SECONDS` (`pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx:1799-1848`) the file jumps straight into state/effects and `getHelpCooldownMs`; there is no `HELP_URGENCY_THRESHOLDS`, `HELP_URGENCY_GROUP`, `getHelpUrgency`, or `getHelpTimerStr`. The v6.0 urgency coloring and timer formatting requested by the task cannot be wired in from this baseline. FIX: insert the two `useMemo` constants immediately after `HELP_COOLDOWN_SECONDS` and add both `useCallback` helpers before the render path.
4. [P1] Fix 4 i18n dictionaries are incomplete for the v6.0 help drawer contract - the EN block at `pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx:525-583` still uses the old keys such as `help.bill` and `help.menu`, and it is missing the new `help.get_bill`, `help.plate`, `help.utensils`, `help.clear_table`, short-label, subtitle, cancel-flow, other-request, and send-button keys. In RU, `pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx:588-603` still keeps the old long `help.get_bill` copy, and the block has no RU `help.sent_suffix` or `help.undo` entry. If Fix 1 is applied on top of this dictionary, several new keys will resolve to raw keys or wrong copy. FIX: add only the new EN/RU keys listed in Fix 4, replace the RU `help.get_bill` value with the shorter label, and leave existing unrelated `help.*` entries untouched.

